Let G be a Group, let A\subseteq  G be a subset. We define the Normalizer of A to be the subgroup N_{G}(A) such that
N_{G}(A)=\{h\in  G\mid  Ah=hA\}
In other words, for any a\in  A and for any h\in  N_{G}(A), we have h^{-1}ah\in  A.

